      "acceptanceCriteria": "Physics assumptions justified by literature or preliminary analysis; all major mechanisms captured.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic titanium alloy constitutive model is appropriate for the elastic regime QoIs (stiffness). Bilinear isotropic hardening is used for post-yield QoIs. Frictional contact (μ=0.3) is applied at screw-rod and rod-block interfaces, consistent with published tribological data for Ti-6Al-4V. Model form uncertainty is bounded by the E/uval metric."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
