    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed the required level for model risk level 3. The Test conditions factor achieves level 2 against a required level of 3; this shortfall is accepted because (a) the ASTM F1717 single-condition protocol is the regulatory standard for this device class, (b) the output comparison metric (E/uval < 1.96) demonstrates adequate predictive accuracy under the tested condition, and (c) the medium model influence and medium decision consequence bound the overall risk. The credibility evidence package is accepted as sufficient to support the regulatory submission claim.",
